WEBVTT



00:00:06.496 --> 00:00:10.816
This is the Gospel of Matthew podcast from Pretty Dub Bay Methodist Church.

00:00:10.912 --> 00:00:11.968
Today,

00:00:11.840 --> 00:00:13.440
February 10th

00:00:13.568 --> 00:00:15.840
And our passage is Matthew 12.

00:00:15.872 --> 00:00:17.440
38 through 50.

00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:18.976
I'm Levi Gardner.

00:00:18.848 --> 00:00:20.448
Thank you for joining us.

00:00:21.472 --> 00:00:24.640
Jesus opens with the illusion

00:00:24.704 --> 00:00:26.944
To the story of Jonah,

00:00:26.720 --> 00:00:28.544
And how it foretells.

00:00:28.544 --> 00:00:30.560
His time in the tomb.

00:00:30.784 --> 00:00:36.160
And he asserts that this sign has been given that there would be no confusion when he.

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:37.408
It performs.

00:00:37.504 --> 00:00:41.184
Or reveals before them the miracle of his resurrection.

00:00:42.080 --> 00:00:43.840
That he lets them know.

00:00:44.096 --> 00:00:46.592
That there is a hardness of heart.

00:00:46.464 --> 00:00:50.176
That he discerns among the scribes and the Pharisees.

00:00:50.432 --> 00:01:00.480
The signs have been given to them before. Jesus is born into the world and the signs are being given in their midst, yet they refuse to see the truth of what God

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:01.920
of what God is pointing to.

00:01:03.136 --> 00:01:05.760
Jesus then begins to share about

00:01:05.664 --> 00:01:07.264
An unclean spirit

00:01:07.808 --> 00:01:09.472
And this is a reminder that

00:01:09.504 --> 00:01:14.688
If there are places of emptiness in our life, evil will seek to take a foothold.

00:01:15.168 --> 00:01:20.704
And this is why we are called to immerse ourselves and to fill every space of our life with Jesus.

00:01:20.992 --> 00:01:25.760
For if Jesus occupies the home, there is no space for the Spirit to return.

00:01:25.920 --> 00:01:32.064
How are we opening the inner places of our heart and our soul for Jesus to dwell?

00:01:32.224 --> 00:01:35.360
How are we allowing Jesus to dwell in our parenting?

00:01:35.552 --> 00:01:36.960
In our marriage

00:01:37.088 --> 00:01:38.368
In our work.

00:01:38.496 --> 00:01:40.096
And our friendships

00:01:40.800 --> 00:01:43.072
May we not seed any ground.

00:01:42.848 --> 00:01:44.032
To the enemy.

00:01:44.256 --> 00:01:46.400
But firmly supplant

00:01:46.176 --> 00:01:47.808
And renew

00:01:47.936 --> 00:01:49.952
And ground all things,

00:01:49.920 --> 00:01:53.184
And the presence and the love and the spirit of Jesus.

00:01:54.752 --> 00:01:57.408
Family, it's something that Jesus

00:01:57.824 --> 00:02:00.800
Has questions about during his ministry.

00:02:01.472 --> 00:02:04.032
And Jesus answers with wisdom.

00:02:04.288 --> 00:02:08.960
For he recognizes he is speaking across all ages and all time.

00:02:09.184 --> 00:02:12.672
The words Jesus offers about family gives hope.

00:02:13.056 --> 00:02:15.232
He leaves no one out.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.288
He says, look, your mother and your brothers are standing outside wanting to speak to you.

00:02:20.736 --> 00:02:25.216
He replied to the one who was speaking to him, Who is my mother and who are my brothers?

00:02:25.664 --> 00:02:30.304
Stretching out his hand toward his disciples, he said, Here are my mother and my brothers.

00:02:30.688 --> 00:02:35.296
For whoever does the will of my Father in heaven is my brother and sister.

00:02:35.040 --> 00:02:36.160
And mother.

00:02:37.440 --> 00:02:38.624
Jesus,

00:02:38.656 --> 00:02:40.768
And his foreknowledge.

00:02:40.896 --> 00:02:45.568
And then the knowledge of the life that he was living saw broken homes,

00:02:45.792 --> 00:02:49.216
Husbands leaving families, wives abandoning.

00:02:49.216 --> 00:02:50.592
their children,

00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:54.368
The brokenness of human relationship on display before him.

00:02:54.944 --> 00:03:00.000
And Jesus is having us to see that God gives a family to all.

00:02:59.808 --> 00:03:02.816
Regardless of the sustainability,

00:03:02.560 --> 00:03:07.456
Or the safety or the predictability or the security of their earthly family.

00:03:08.160 --> 00:03:10.880
That in Christ we are

00:03:10.944 --> 00:03:13.120
adopted into God's family.

00:03:13.088 --> 00:03:15.200
As sons and daughters.

00:03:15.872 --> 00:03:19.424
In the family of our one true and eternal father.

00:03:19.776 --> 00:03:21.664
This is a word of hope.

00:03:22.240 --> 00:03:24.480
That when we do the will of Christ,

00:03:24.640 --> 00:03:26.336
He calls us son.

00:03:26.176 --> 00:03:27.264
Or daughter.

00:03:27.680 --> 00:03:30.976
And he points to his father as your father.

00:03:31.392 --> 00:03:32.832
As my father.

00:03:33.408 --> 00:03:35.328
This is

00:03:35.520 --> 00:03:37.696
The promise of Christ.

00:03:38.368 --> 00:03:40.448
If your family is far

00:03:40.480 --> 00:03:42.368
From stable,

00:03:42.784 --> 00:03:44.256
If you've yearned

00:03:44.192 --> 00:03:45.728
To have a family.

00:03:46.272 --> 00:03:48.480
Hear the promise of Christ.

00:03:48.384 --> 00:03:49.568
In him.

00:03:49.536 --> 00:03:52.128
is the family that God is establishing.

00:03:52.032 --> 00:03:53.664
That will never fade.

00:03:53.568 --> 00:03:55.168
That will never fail.

00:03:55.136 --> 00:03:57.664
That will always be there.

00:03:57.984 --> 00:03:59.072
And it is

00:03:59.008 --> 00:04:01.920
led by our perfect and Heavenly Father.

00:04:01.888 --> 00:04:05.248
They will always be loving to you

00:04:05.376 --> 00:04:08.320
Who will always have your best interest in mind.

00:04:08.448 --> 00:04:14.464
And who gives you his wisdom and the Holy Spirit that you might lead the life that he desires for you to live.

00:04:15.328 --> 00:04:17.248
This chapter is full of

00:04:17.088 --> 00:04:18.592
Of promises

00:04:18.816 --> 00:04:20.352
Full of warnings.

00:04:20.832 --> 00:04:25.344
Full of Christ pointing us once again to who he is.

00:04:25.504 --> 00:04:29.664
Who his father is, and how we are to find our place in his family.

00:04:29.568 --> 00:04:33.504
And then the power of what Jesus promises in his life and his death.

00:04:33.248 --> 00:04:34.784
And there's resurrection.

00:04:35.168 --> 00:04:38.048
Our producer for today's podcast is Kenny Stewart.

00:04:37.824 --> 00:04:39.552
I'm Levi Gardner.
